Explain didactically how the following mutual exclusion algorithm works. I don't want you to explain each line, I want to understand the operating principles. What makes it implement mutual exclusion?
```java
//N is the number of threads in the system
//vector is initialized to False
boolean[] intents = new boolean[N];

void lock() {
    int id = Thread.getID();
    intents[id] = false;
    for (int j = 0; j < id; j += 1) {
        if (intents[j])
            goto L0;
    }
    intents[id] = true;
    for (int j = 0; j < id; j += 1) {
        if (intents[j]) {
            goto L0;
        }
    }
    for (int i = id + 1; i < N; j += 1) {
        if (intents[j]) {
            goto L0;
        }
    }
}

void unlock() {
    intents[id] = false;
}
```

